The paper deals with the k-Path and k-Cycle problems in various restricted graph classes, such as planar graphs, graphs of bounded degree, and claw-free graphs. These are all topics that fall under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from computational geometry, which is a subfield of Computer Graphics (cs.CG). The use of oracle machines and polynomial-time algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problems in terms of graph theory, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the use of colored k-Path, which is a topic in Graph Theory (cs.GT).
